# CI parity — local checks can lie

When a developer reports "my local check passes but CI failed", do NOT default to "must be a CI flake" or "must be a stale CI cache". There are **four documented mechanisms** by which local static-analysis checks (lint, typecheck, README/link checkers) silently disagree with CI. The first three were isolated 2026-05-19 during sub-plan #9 slot 7 (umbraculum-dev `docs/design/brewery-scope-migration-plan.md` §6.7); mechanism 4 surfaced 2026-05-28 during OpenAPI alpha. The lesson applies to every TS/JS monorepo.

## Container-only execution (cross-platform)

CI parity checks **must run inside Docker**, using the **same image CI uses** (default `node:20-slim` — read the workflow file; do not assume). The host shell only orchestrates `git archive` + `docker run`; **never** run `npm` / `npx tsc` / `npm run lint` on the host for parity verification.

- **Why:** Matches GitHub Actions (`ubuntu-latest` + container), eliminates host Node version drift (Linux / macOS / WSL), and avoids bind-mounting the live workspace (mechanism 3).
- **Prerequisites on the developer machine:** `git`, Docker, and Node.js (to run `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity`). Bash is required only for the optional `scripts/ci-parity-check.sh` wrapper on Unix — **not** for the canonical cross-platform path. Docker Desktop on macOS/Windows; WSL2 is the supported Windows path for compose-heavy debug; native Windows `cmd` without Docker is out of scope.
- **Canonical pre-push (umbraculum-dev):** after **commit**, with a **clean working tree**, run `npm run verify:pre-push` (T2-PR: path-aware parallel ci-parity) or `npm run verify:pre-push:release` (T2-release: full sequential manifest). **`--ci`** (wrapper default) is for **WIP iteration only**, not the push gate.
- **Long-running dev containers** (`docker compose exec api npm run typecheck`, etc.) are fine for fast iteration but are **not** CI parity — different `node_modules` layout (see mechanism 4).

## Rule (hard)

When CI fails on a check that you (or the developer) ran locally and saw green:

1. **Do not push another commit hoping to "see what CI says" again.** That treats CI as a remote test runner and burns ~3–5 min per round-trip per job.
2. **Reproduce the CI job in a clean `git archive HEAD` snapshot** — not in the live workspace — and confirm the failure locally. Then fix locally. Then re-verify in the snapshot. Then push.
3. The runbook for this is **`ci-parity-local-reproduction`** skill (in this plugin).
4. If the repo ships a `scripts/ci-parity-check.sh` (thin wrapper) or `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json`, prefer `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity` — one command, ~2 min, all jobs from the manifest.

## The four divergence mechanisms — check each one when local and CI disagree

| # | Mechanism | Symptom in CI | Root-cause check |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Gitignored cross-references** | Tracked README's relative link 404s in CI; resolves locally. | `git check-ignore -v <relative-link-target>` — if non-empty, the file is .gitignored. CI's `actions/checkout@v5` brings tracked files only; your host has the local copy. **Fix:** point the link at a tracked alternative (root `README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT-LOCAL.md`, etc.) or remove. |
| 2 | **Nested-workspace install drift** | TS2307 "Cannot find module 'X'" for a workspace's devDep; locally resolves. | `grep workspaces <repo>/package.json` — if root `workspaces:` is a one-level glob (`apps/*`, `services/*`, `packages/*`), nested workspaces TWO levels deep (e.g. `apps/web/e2e`) are NOT installed by `npm install --workspaces`. Locally hidden by stale `<workspace>/node_modules` from prior manual installs (bind-mounted into your docker reproduction). **Fix:** add an explicit `cd <nested-ws> && npm install` step to every CI workflow that touches it. |
| 3 | **Stale `<workspace>/node_modules` bind-mount shadowing** | Lint rule fires in CI but is silent locally; or type-aware rule behavior diverges. | Run `ls <workspace>/node_modules/` on your host — if non-empty, your docker reproductions see it via bind-mount **when you mount the live workspace**. Type-aware ESLint rules (notably `@typescript-eslint/require-await`, `@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises`) can fire differently depending on whether transitive types resolve. **Fix:** reproduce in a clean `git archive HEAD` snapshot under `/tmp/`, not in the live workspace. |
| 4 | **Workspace hoisting splits** | TS2339 / missing plugin augmentation in CI only; passes in a workspace-local or flat dev-container install. | Root `npm ci --workspaces` hoists some packages to `/repo/node_modules` while peers stay in `<workspace>/node_modules`. TypeScript `declare module` augmentations from the hoisted copy may not merge onto types resolved from the workspace copy. **Fix:** verify under the hoisted install (CI-parity snapshot); add a local `.d.ts` augmentation co-located with the workspace's dependency tree if needed. |

## Authoring-time guardrails (apply when writing READMEs / CI workflows / lint configs)

- **README links** — never link from a tracked file to a `.gitignored` path. Specifically forbidden in this repo: `[DEVELOPMENT.md](...)` from any tracked README (the file is per-developer, gitignored). Use the root `README.md` or `DEVELOPMENT-LOCAL.md` (tracked template) instead.
- **CI workflows** — for every workspace not matched by the root `workspaces:` glob (today: only `apps/web/e2e`, but future nested workspaces are analogous), every CI workflow that depends on it must `cd <ws> && npm install` explicitly after the root `npm install --workspaces`. Add an inline comment so the next maintainer understands the gap.
- **Pre-push (two tiers — agent-owned)** — when **you** will push non-trivial CI surface, **you** run the gate; do not tell the operator to run it:
  1. **Commit** intended changes first (archive mode does not see uncommitted fixes).
  2. **Static analysis:** `npm run verify:pre-push` (T2-PR) when the repo ships `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json` and `.umbraculum/gha-trigger-map.json` (umbraculum-dev does). Resolves only GHA-triggered jobs; runs them **in parallel** with `--isolated-install`. Use `npm run verify:pre-push:release` for manifest/pin/SDK tag prep (all 5 jobs, sequential). **`--ci`** is WIP-only — not push proof.
  3. **API integration:** T2-PR auto-runs vitest when `api.yml` paths match. When outside the resolver, run skill **`api-integration-tests-pre-push`**. Rule **`75-api-integration-pre-push-gate`**.
- **New GHA workflows** — add equivalent verify steps to `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json` as a named job; workflows and local pre-push must not diverge. Do not document host-only `python3` / `bash` one-liners as the pre-push gate.

## Agent anti-patterns (hard)

Agents **must not** treat any of the following as sufficient pre-push verification or as a substitute for ci-parity:

| Anti-pattern | Why it fails |
|---|---|
| `python3 scripts/docs/check-….py` on the host | Unix-biased; skips `git archive` snapshot; not what GHA runs in isolation |
| `./scripts/build-packages-in-docker.sh` or scoped `docker run … bash -lc` on live `$PWD` | Not manifest-driven; mount may include stale host `node_modules` (mechanism 3) |
| `docker compose exec api npm run …` | Dev-container layout ≠ CI hoisting (mechanism 4); also **not** the GHA `api` vitest job |
| `docker compose exec api npm test` without checking vitest **Unhandled Errors** | CI fails on unhandled rejections even when all tests pass |
| "CI will tell us" / push to discover failures | Burns GHA minutes; ci-parity exists to avoid this |
| Push without `--archive` after commit (only `--ci` during WIP) | GHA runs committed code; uncommitted local fixes hide broken `HEAD` |
| Ending a session with "run verify:pre-push before you push" | Pre-push is **agent-owned** — run T2 yourself per umbraculum-dev `AGENTS.md` |
| Full sequential manifest on every feature push | Use T2-PR (`verify:pre-push`); reserve T2-release for manifest/pin/SDK tag prep |
| Host `npm view` / host `./scripts/*-smoke.sh` / host npm polling | Host is not the project; Node/npm skew yields false red/green — use `node:20-slim` or ci-parity (rule `00-shared-node-npm-container-only`) |

**Required before push (umbraculum-dev — agents run this, not the operator):**

1. Commit all intended changes; working tree clean.
2. **Static analysis:** `npm run verify:pre-push` (T2-PR — path-aware parallel jobs) or `npm run verify:pre-push:release` (T2-release).
3. **API integration:** included in T2-PR when resolver matches `api.yml` paths; otherwise skill **`api-integration-tests-pre-push`**.
4. Push only after steps 2–3 are green.

**Allowed for local debug** (operator or agent, after ci-parity fails or during tight edit loop): compose exec, host scripts, live-tree docker — label these as debug, not as push gates.

